    <stitle>AIR CONDITIONING - HEATER SYSTEM: 5000, 9000 Series Without Lowered heater Box - MAINTENANCE - AIR FILTER
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="pm" graphiccount="1">
        <title>AIR FILTER</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>The air conditioning system air filter element should be replaced every year at the beginning of the
                cooling season. More frequent replacement may be required for vehicles operating in dusty areas.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove and Install</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the passenger seat and cover from the top of the Blend-Air unit.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lift the old element from the unit, noting the orientation of the filter construction (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601511">Figure 11</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1601511" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic id="g1601509" filename="../figg16/G1601509A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 11. Air Filter</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. EVAPORATOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. FILTER ELEMENT</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. BLOWER HOUSING</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the new filter element in the slot between the blower housing and the
                    evaporator. Make sure that the matted or net side of the filter faces the evaporator and the loose
                    bristle ends face the blower.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Reinstall the Blend-Air unit cover and passenger seat.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
